OBINNA EZUGWU President Muhammadu Buhari will make a New Year broadcast to the nation Friday, January 1, 2021 at 7am, presidential spokesperson, Mallam Garba Shehu has said. Shehu who made the announcement in a statement on Thursday, asked all television and radio stations in the country to join the Nigerian Television Authority for the broadcast. “Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to join the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively, for the broadcast,” he said.